answers.body_markdown:
Please note that [ID selector](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/ID_selectors) is supposed to be unique in a HTML document. And jQuery [expects that to be true](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11114622/jquery-id-selector-works-only-for-the-first-element). So instead of using ID, you should use class name for the delete button

```javascript
$(&#39;.deletebutton&#39;).click(function(){
  var pcode = $(this).data(&#39;id&#39;);
  $(&#39;#deleteproject&#39;).data(&#39;id&#39;, pcode); 
});

//...
```
```php
&lt;button
  class=&quot;deletebutton btn btn-danger btn-xs&quot;
  data-toggle=&quot;modal&quot;
  data-target=&quot;#deletemodal&quot;
  data-id=&quot;&lt;?php echo $row-&gt;project_code;?&gt;&quot;
&gt;
  &lt;span class = &quot;fa fa-trash-o&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Delete
&lt;/button&gt;
```

Assuming your `showproject()` function won&#39;t accidentally remove / recreate your `#deleteproject` button, things should work for you.

